# Figma icons — frame vs glyph (no stretching)

When implementing icons from Figma exports in `web/`, **never size the `<img>` to the frame dimension**. Figma filenames like `close-24.svg` or `flag-16.svg` usually name the **container/frame**, not the drawable.

## The rule

1. **Frame (container)** — CSS on the button, pill, or slot (e.g. `40×40` circle with `8px` padding, or a `24×24` / `20×20` grid slot).
2. **Glyph (artwork)** — size from the SVG **`viewBox`** (intrinsic width × height), centered inside the frame with `display: grid; place-items: center` or flex centering.

Exported Figma SVGs often use `width="100%" height="100%"` and `preserveAspectRatio="none"`. Forcing `pe-icon-24` (24×24) on those assets **stretches** the glyph.

## Implementation pattern

```html
<!-- 40×40 frame (pe-menu-btn), 24×24 inner slot, ~13.5×13.5 glyph -->
<button class="pe-menu-btn" type="button" aria-label="…">
  <img class="pe-glyph pe-glyph--close-24" src="…/close-24.svg" alt="" />
</button>

<!-- Or explicit slot wrapper -->
<span class="pe-foot-icon-slot">
  <img class="pe-glyph pe-glyph--arrow-left-20" src="…/arrow-left-20.svg" alt="" />
</span>
```

```css
.pe-foot-icon-slot {
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.pe-glyph {
  display: block;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  object-fit: contain;
  max-width: none;
  max-height: none;
}

/* Size from viewBox, e.g. viewBox="0 0 13.5 13.5" → 13.5px × 13.5px */
.pe-glyph--close-24 {
  width: 13.5px;
  height: 13.5px;
}
```

## When adding a new icon

1. Open the SVG and read **`viewBox`** (e.g. `0 0 13.5 7.29` → glyph is ~13.5×7.29px).
2. Add `.pe-glyph--<asset-name>` in `practice-exam.css` (or the screen’s CSS) with those dimensions.
3. Wrap in a frame element sized to **Figma’s container** (pill, chip, legend dot, etc.).
4. Use `class="pe-glyph pe-glyph--…"` on the `<img>`, not `pe-icon-24` / `pe-icon-20`, unless viewBox equals the frame.

## Do not

- Put `width: 24px; height: 24px` on every icon inside a 24px Figma frame.
- Use global `img { max-width: 100% }` without exempting glyphs (breaks slots). Prefer `img.pe-glyph { max-width: none; max-height: none; }`.
- Assume filename suffix (`-24`, `-16`) is the render size of the path.

## Reference

Working examples: `web/css/practice-exam.css` (`.pe-glyph`, `.pe-glyph--*`, `.pe-*-icon-slot`, `.pe-results-exit-slot`), Practice Exam session/results/review screens.

`pe-icon-24` / `pe-icon-20` / `pe-icon-16` are only for assets whose **viewBox matches** that box (e.g. some non-Figma icons).
